As of the [[census]]<ref name="GR2">{{cite web|url=https://www.census.gov|publisher=[[United States Census Bureau]]|access-date=2008-01-31 |df=mdy-all|title=U.S. Census website}}</ref> of 2000, there were 9 people, 4 households, and 3 families residing in the village. The [[population density]] was {{convert|83.0|PD/sqmi|PD/sqkm|1|abbr=on}}. There were 5 housing units at an average density of {{convert|46.1|/sqmi|/sqkm|abbr=on}}. The racial makeup of the village was 7 [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 1 [[Pacific Islander (U.S. Census)|Pacific Islander]], 1 from [[Race (United States Census)|other races]]. There were 2 [[Hispanic (U.S. Census)|Hispanics]] or [[Latino (U.S. Census)|Latinos]] of any race.

There were four households, none of which had children under the age of 18 living with them. Two were [[Marriage|married couples]] living together, one had a female householder with no husband present, and one was a non-family. One household was made up of individuals, and one had someone living alone who was 65 years of age or older. The average household size was 2.25 and the average family size was 2.67.

In the village two people were under the age of 18, both girls. There was one person from 18 to 24, one from 25 to 44, two from 45 to 64, and three who were 65 years of age or older. The median age was 48 years. There were seven females and two males.
